external_knowledge:
- "shining stars of the music scene" refers to tracks with the highest average popularity;
- "celebrated performers" refers to the artists who perform these tracks;
- "radiant glow of their average user ratings" refers to the average popularity of tracks as calculated by averaging user ratings.

Popularity score refers to the sum of all ratings; higher scores indicate higher popularity; the term 'most highly rated' means the top tracks based on user ratings.;
Tracks with higher ratings are typically considered more popular among listeners.;
The limit of 10 tracks is intended to showcase only the most popular ones.;

sql:
SELECT track_name
FROM tracks
WHERE track_id < 10;

SELECT AVG(age) AS average_age
FROM user_profiles
WHERE date_joined BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';

